## Summary

| Severity | Count | Pattern |
|----------|-------|---------|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 | **No assertions at all** — methods called, results ignored |
| 🟠 High | 3 | **`IsNotNull`-only** — asserts existence, not correctness |
| 🟡 Medium | 4 | **Missing negative/edge cases** — only happy path covered |

**Root cause:** Every test follows a "call it and pray" pattern — the 95% coverage number reflects *lines executed*, not *behavior verified*. A mutation testing tool (e.g., Stryker.NET) would show a near-0% mutation kill rate, which is the real coverage metric.
